It helps the raid and my guild defeat the mobs, end of story.  I like the idea of playing as a team and everyone doing their part.<br>
<br>
That said, I do nuke when there are enough rods, I do summon a pet when at a boss like mob (vt bosses, and such), and I CoH when needed.  I figure that the mages that hate making rods would rather be more offense orientated, which is fine, just get in a guild with alot of mages.  The guild I am in usually has 3+ mages at a raid, and all of us can nuke and rod, and trusty Jobaner at our sides.<br>
